Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editAdjust(25.10)                                            editAdjust(25.10)

Name
       editAdjust  -  Aligns  wires and pins on the basis of the specified op-
       tions

Syntax
       editAdjust

       [-help]

       [-adjust_size]

       -refer_obj {top bottom left right}

       {[-align_edge  {left  center  right  top   middle   bottom   diag45_top
       diag45_middle diag45_bottom diag135_top diag135_middle diag135_bottom}]

        [-space_mode {horizontal vertical dist_horizontal dist_vertical diag45
       diag135 dist_diag45 dist_diag135}

          [-space <float_value>]]}

       Aligns  wires  and pins on the basis of the specified options. The fol-
       lowing objects can be aligned using this command:

              *

                Regular, special, and patch wires

              *

                Physical pins

              *

                Macro pins

       The editAdjust command enables you to align objects in one or  both  of
       the following modes:

              * Align  by edge: Use the -align_edge parameter to align objects
                with the reference object by the specified edge.

              * Align with spacing: Use the -space_mode  parameter  to  adjust
                the spacing between objects.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editAdjust parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editAdjust

       -adjust_size
              Resizes the objects being aligned to match the reference object.
              If  -align_edge  is specified, the specified edge of the objects
              is stretched or shrunk to align with the edge of  the  reference
              object.  If  -space_mode is specified, the objects being aligned
              are resized to be equal to the reference object.

       -align_edge {left center right top middle bottom diag45_top diag45_mid-
       dle diag45_bottom diag135_top diag135_middle diag135_bottom}
              Specifies the edge by which the objects should be  aligned  with
              the reference object.

       -refer_obj {top bottom left right}
              Specifies  the  object  of reference for alignment. For example,
              -refer_obj left means that objects should be aligned with refer-
              ence to the leftmost object.

              This option is mandatory.

       -space <float_value>
              Specifies the spacing value for aligning objects  in  the  space
              mode. This option can be specified only if -space_mode is speci-
              fied.

       -space_mode {horizontal vertical dist_horizontal dist_vertical diag45
       diag135 dist_diag45 dist_diag135}
              Specifies  that  objects should be aligned in the space mode. In
              this mode, the objects are aligned  such  that  there  is  equal
              spacing between them. You can specify one of the following space
              mode options:

              * horizontal - Aligns the objects such that the horizontal spac-
                ing between them is equal to the value specified with -space.

              * vertical  -  Aligns the objects such that the vertical spacing
                between them is equal to the value specified with -space.

              * dist_horizontal - Distributes the objects horizontally.

              * dist_vertical - Distributes the objects vertically.

              * diag45 - Aligns the objects in the  45-degree  direction  such
                that  the spacing between them is equal to the value specified
                with -space.

              * diag135 - Aligns the objects in the 135-degree direction  such
                that  the spacing between them is equal to the value specified
                with -space.

              * dist_diag45 - Distributes the objects in the 45-degree  direc-
                tion.

              * dist_diag135  -  Distributes the objects in the 135-degree di-
                rection.

Examples
              *

                The following command aligns the left edge of  all  the  wires
                using the leftmost object as reference:

                editAdjust -align_edge left -refer_obj left

              *

                The  following command uses the leftmost wire as reference and
                resizes the other wires so that their left  edges  align  with
                the left edge of the reference wire:

                editAdjust -align_edge left -refer_obj left -adjust_size

              *

                The following command aligns the center of all the wires using
                the leftmost object as reference:

                editAdjust -align_edge center -refer_obj left

              *

                The  following  command aligns the right edge of all the wires
                using the leftmost object as reference:

                editAdjust -align_edge right -refer_obj left

              *

                The following command aligns the top edge of all the wires us-
                ing the leftmost object as reference:

                editAdjust -align_edge top -refer_obj left

              *

                The following command aligns the bottom edge of all the  wires
                using the leftmost object as reference:

                editAdjust -align_edge bottom -refer_obj left

              * The  following  command  uses the leftmost object as reference
                and aligns the wires in the horizontal direction in the  space
                mode with a spacing of 5 units:

                editAdjust -space_mode horizontal -space 5 -refer_obj left

              * The  following  command  uses the leftmost object as reference
                and aligns the wires in the horizontal direction in the  space
                mode  with  a spacing of 5 units. The command also resizes the
                objects being aligned to match the reference object:

                editAdjust -space_mode horizontal  -space  5  -refer_obj  left
                -adjust_size

              *

                The  following  command  uses the leftmost object as reference
                and aligns the wires in the vertical direction  in  the  space
                mode with a spacing of 15 units:

                editAdjust -space_mode vertical -space 15 -refer_obj left

              *

                The  following  command  uses the leftmost object as reference
                and distributes the wires horizontally:

                editAdjust -space_mode dist_horizontal -refer_obj left

              *

                The following command uses the leftmost  object  as  reference
                and distributes the wires vertically:

                editAdjust -space_mode dist_vertical -refer_obj left

              *

                The  following  command  uses the leftmost object as reference
                and aligns the left edge of all the wires, keeping  a  spacing
                of 5 units between the wires in the vertical direction:

                editAdjust -align_edge left -space_mode vertical -space 5 -re-
                fer_obj left

              * The  following  command  uses the leftmost object as reference
                and aligns the wires in the 135-degree direction in the  space
                mode with a spacing of 5 units:

                editAdjust -space_mode diag135 -space 5.0 -refer_obj left

